TITLE: Austin police release bodycam footage of shootout with armed suspect hiding on restaurant's patio
SUMMARY: Body camera footage released by the Austin Police Department shows officers exchanging gunfire with a suspect who was displaying a gun in a "threatening manner."

TITLE: Two men arrested after wild police chase with baby in car
SUMMARY: Two men and a woman ended up arrested following a police chase in the Dallas area where a baby was on board. Police have not said what the involved were wanted for to begin with.

TITLE: Florida medical boards approve ban on puberty blockers, transgender surgeries for minors
SUMMARY: The Florida Board of Medicine and the Florida Board of Osteopathic Medicine voted last week to ban puberty blockers and other gender dysphoria treatments for minors in Florida.

TITLE: Seattle firefighters rescue 13-year-old boy trapped inside car after crash in parking lot
SUMMARY: A 13-year-old boy was rescued after he became trapped inside a car that crashed in a parking lot in Seattle and tipped over a railing on Saturday, officials said.

TITLE: Ohio postal worker busted in fentanyl trafficking operation
SUMMARY: A postal service supervisor in Cincinnati pleaded guilty after being involved in a scheme to intercept packages containing illegal drugs and delivering them himself.

TITLE: Utah man ‘upset’ over canceled flight carjacks multiple vehicles, causes crashes: police
SUMMARY: John Green, 20, faces multiple felony charges after allegedly carjacking two vehicles, trying to carjack two others and causing numerous crashes around Salt Lake City.

TITLE: Georgia 'Blue Alert' suspect still on the run after investigators discover car
SUMMARY: Investigators have located the car a man at the center of a "Blue Alert" in Georgia allegedly took off from the scene of a shooting that left a detention officer injured and another person dead.

TITLE: Florida burglary suspect arrested after neighbor, dog find trail of blood leading into home: deputies
SUMMARY: A man walking his dog in Brevard County, Florida, on Tuesday morning discovered a trail of blood leading into his neighbor's home and led deputies to a suspected burglar.

TITLE: Ex-NYPD officer found guilty in murder of 8-year-old son
SUMMARY: Michael Valva, a former NYPD officer, was found guilty of killing his 8-year-old son in January 2020. He was found guilty on all charges, including second-degree murder.

TITLE: At least 9 injured in mass shooting outside Philadelphia bar: police
SUMMARY: An investigation is underway in Philadelphia after a mass shooting injured at least nine people, two critically, in the city's Kensington neighborhood Saturday night.
